This program adds two integer numbers and displays the result. It declares two variables and stores numeric values in them. The addition operator (+) is used to calculate the sum. Finally, the result is printed on the screen. This program introduces arithmetic operations in Java.
public class AddNumbers {
public static void main(String[] args) {
int a = 10;
int b = 20;
int sum = a + b;
System.out.println("Sum = " + sum);
}
}Output :
Sum = 30
